inline_comments.message:
@Eric: as @Bartek said, replacing this symlink by a static file disables its content management by systemd-resolved.

@Bartek: systemd-resolved config is rendered from netplan YAMLs ("/etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml": https://github.com/lavabit/robox/blob/806fc9412a9a4164945b106f5f6ae53741d3baa2/scripts/ubuntu1804/network.sh#L44); I can change those, then apply generated config - providing static single line file seemed to be simpler solution.

Redirection to "tee" was used to have it logged in provisioner output.

Further explanation in comment to "host_ip" variable above.
